   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fourth year of the new era: September</h2>

<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 1st, Mia Handur thanks those that donated for the new orphanage by their names. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 1st, Alora Ironforge warns of the Town Guard warns of the subject Konstantin, who injured Mia Handur in order to use her blood in a dark ritual and resurrect his dead fianc&eacute;e Irania. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 2nd, Malvita remembers a conversation with Hirathe the Priest, which encourages him in his faith to his Goddess. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 2nd, the Grey Rose invites the island populace to an open party in their castle. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 4th, Nedor von Largon offers his lute in a trade for twenty healing potions. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 4th, the pain of the ravaged forests is sung of by the poems of an anonymous person named "Watcher of the Woods" for the first time. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 5th, the Triumvirate--consisting of John Irenicus, Captain of the Guard, Lennier, Earl of the Grey Rose, and Fedaykin—- assumes regency over Troll's Bane and replaces Lyrenzia. This is supported by the Town Guard and the Grey Rose, as well as Silverbrand. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 5th, in conclusion to the Triumvirate's stemming from Lyrenzia, Trystan Gravstyn suggests a government to be chosen by the people—-this suggestion comes into a heavy crossfire of critique. Others like Malvita Rynal suggest themselves to be the new government. Heated debates erupt between supporters and naysayers. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 5th, the Triumvirate publishes a list of all the people with voting rights in the coming council election. Trystan Gravstyn then tries to establish a council himself. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 6th, Cliu Beothach presents his election platform for the choice of the Triumvirate's third member. Others, like Domitrio, Caitlin Fergus, and Sherri, also present their platforms in the following days. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 7th, Latheliar seeks a seasoned forester for the Elven Realm. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 8th, Kasume suffers an attack in Eliza's Shop—perhaps because of mushrooms—and he injures those who intend to help him. Later on, he accuses his helpers—Mia Handur, Shandariel el Lysanthrai, Sideon Vilarion, and Rith Orion—of attempted murder. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 9th, Malvita calls the citizens to join his group "Voice for the People", who oppose the regime change of the Triumvirate. The group descends into insignificance. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 9th, Brendan Mason presents a complaint in the name of Greenbriar, that Burlow Boincloud opened an orphanage for Mia Handur in a house of Greenbriar without having asked the owners for permission. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 10th, Rackere Diplomatre launches yet another new vote for the name of the island. This leads to a final ballot between the names Aandar and Gobaith. This voting is terminated by October the 7th because the number of protests increases; these protests state that Aandar originates from a dark tongue. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 11th, Jeremy Willowbrook publishes the story of his life in order to excuse himself to his friends.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 12th, Val de Gausse dies in a conflict with Gwynnether. His corpse is burnt in the stone circle and his ashes are dispersed into all winds.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 13th, Veralion, Chief of the Bloodskulls, announces that the Blood Territory is now also open to new settlers. </p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 27th, Gwynnether is severely injured by Trolls during an attack on the town. Galim and Caitlin Fergus nurse her.</p>
<p>In the fourth year of the new era on September the 30th, the Orc Grunith Shuth attacks his own Shaman Kaja in an unfounded outburst of berserker rage. Days later, he is being held in the tavern—his spirit is clouded.</p>

